{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7f2f16b7-ad10-4eef-8544-158903b149a8","content":"The workflow is at `.github/workflows/publish.yml`.\n\n## How It Works\n\n| Concern | How it's handled |\n|---|---|\n| **Authentication** | GitHub OIDC mints a short-lived token proving the run's identity (repo, workflow, environment). NuGet.org verifies it against your trusted publisher config — no secrets needed. |\n| **Trigger** | Pushing a tag like `v1.2.3` starts the pipeline. |\n| **Scoping** | The `nuget-publish` environment lets you add branch/tag protection rules and required reviewers in GitHub. |\n| **Version** | Set `<Version>` in your `.csproj` or pass `-p:Version=...` at pack time. |\n\n## To Publish a Release\n\n```bash\ngit tag v1.0.0\ngit push origin v1.0.0\n```\n\nThe key insight: `id-token: write` + the `environment` name are what let NuGet.org verify the request without any stored API key.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ad4e7a3e-150d-4835-aa86-84eec01cd939","outputTokens":240},"id":"971bcd8c-ec93-4743-9acf-80f1581f25d9","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:40:12.908Z","parentId":"a79f6859-71f8-473b-b93b-2b4ef7e86c4b"}
